Class ElementSelector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.codename1.rad.io.ElementSelector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Element>, Collection<Element>, Set<Element>

    public class ElementSelector
extends Object
implements Iterable<Element>, Set<Element>

    A query selector similar to the ComponentSelector for working with XML documents.

    shannah

      • ElementSelector

        public ElementSelector(Set<Element> cmps)

        Creates a component selector that wraps the provided components. The provided components are treated as the "results" of this selector. Not the roots. However you can use find(java.lang.String) to perform a query using this selector as the roots.

        Parameters:
        cmps - Components to add to this selector results.

      • ElementSelector

        public ElementSelector(Element... els)

        Creates a element selector that wraps the provided elements. The provided components are treated as the "results" of this selector. Not the roots. However you can use find(java.lang.String) to perform a query using this selector as the roots.

        Parameters:
        els - Components to add to this selector results.

      • ElementSelector

        public ElementSelector(String selector,
                       Element... roots)

        Creates a selector with the provided roots. This will only search through the subtrees of the provided roots to find results that match the provided selector string.

        Parameters:
        selector - The selector string
        roots - The roots for this selector.

      • ElementSelector

        public String getString(String key,

        Parameters:
        key - The key. E.g. "@attname" for attribute. "tagname" for subtag. "subselector/@attname", "subselector/tagname"
